org.jsapar.compose.bean

Interface BeanFactory<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - common base class of all the expected beans. Use Object as base class if there is no common base class for all beans.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BeanFactoryByMap, BeanFactoryDefault

    public interface BeanFactory<T>
    Interface for a bean factory that creates bean instances based on line content. Create your own implementation of this interface if you need to be able to control how beans are created in more details.
    See Also:
    BeanFactoryDefault

    • Method Detail

      • createBean

        T createBean(Line line)
      throws ClassNotFoundException,
             InstantiationException,
             IllegalAccessException,
             ClassCastException
        Parameters:
        line - The line to create a bean for.
        Returns:
        A new instance of a java bean created for the supplied line. If this method returns null, the behavior of the BeanComposer is denoted by the config parameter BeanComposeConfig.setOnUndefinedLineType(ValidationAction)
        Throws:
        ClassNotFoundException - In case any of the classes described in the schema does not exist in the classpath.
        IllegalAccessException - In case a setter method is not publicly accessible.
        InstantiationException - If it was not possible to instantiate a bean.
        ClassCastException - In case an illegal cast is done while trying to use a setter.

      • assignCellToBean

        void assignCellToBean(String lineType,
                      T bean,
                      Cell cell)
               throws BeanComposeException,
                      InvocationTargetException,
                      InstantiationException,
                      IllegalAccessException
        Should assign the value of the specified cell to the proper bean property.
        Parameters:
        lineType - The name of the line type to use.
        bean - The bean to assign to.
        cell - The cell to assign.
        Throws:
        BeanComposeException - In case there is an error assigning the cell. This exception will be caught by the calling BeanComposer and converted into an ErrorEvent.
        InvocationTargetException - If not possible to invoke method.
        IllegalAccessException - In case a setter method is not publicly accessible.
        InstantiationException - If it was not possible to instantiate a bean.
